ity of understandings that the term inspires, this book aims to advance nonsense as a developing critical field, and to inspire new areas of research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNonsense literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Essays.2bisacsh1 aBarton, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarton, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChiarini, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDubois, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFall, Rebecca L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiammei, Alessandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaughton, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeyman, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Freya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirk, Jordan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLukes, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasud, Noreen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiette, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotter, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRann, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoberts, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSatpathy, Sumanyu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwaab, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWestwood, Cassie, econtributor.4ctb4https://i